==Notes==
: It&#x27;s a common pitfall to translate the German &quot;kooperativ&quot; into &quot;cooperative&quot; in English. However, this is a so-called false friend. The English word &quot;cooperative&quot; describes either a business/organisation that is fully owned by the people that work for it (i.e. &quot;Genossenschaft&quot; in German), or it describes someone&#x27;s &quot;willingness&quot; to act or work together, as opposed to their resistance/refusal to acting/working together (=&quot;sich kooperativ zeigen&quot; in German).

