<doc id="375854" wikidata="Q8037055" url="?curid=375854" title="Worshipful Company of Launderers">
<text>The Worshipful Company of Launderers is one of the livery companies of the City of London. The organisation, founded in 1960, became a Livery Company in 1977. It was incorporated by Charter 2010. The Company promotes the profession of the launderers by awarding scholarships to laundry students.

The Launderers&#x27; Company ranks eighty-ninth in the order of precedence for Livery Companies. The Company&#x27;s motto is &quot;Cleanliness is next to Godliness.&quot; Its Chaplain is The Very Reverend Andrew Nunn and its church is Southwark Cathedral.

